President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Rosemary DiCarlo was nominated as the United States Deputy Representative to the United Nations. Brooke D. Anderson was nominated as the Alternate Representative of the United States of America for Special Political Affairs to the United Nations. Douglas B. Wilson was nominated as the Assistant Secretary of Defense for Public Affairs. Malcolm Ross O'Neill was nominated as the Assistant Secretary of the Army (Acquisition, Logistics, and Technology). Jackalyne Pfannenstiel was nominated as the Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Installations and Environment). Donald L. Cook was nominated as the Deputy Administrator for Defense Programs, National Nuclear Security Administration. President Obama expressed his honor in having these individuals join his administration and serve the country.